3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly using a premium index based on the perpetual-spot price difference, with rates applied every hour at the top of each hour. The exchange's Sui-based architecture enables near-instant settlement of funding payments with minimal gas costs. Funding rates are capped at ±2% per hour to prevent extreme scenarios, while the TWAP-based calculation smooths out short-term volatility in the premium calculation."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PYTH","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PYTH's infrastructure utility creates distinct funding patterns compared to speculative tokens, often showing negative rates during oracle data demand spikes. The token's correlation with broader DeFi activity and data provider adoption creates predictable funding cycles that experienced arbitrageurs can exploit. Bluefin's low maker fees and hourly funding frequency make it particularly suitable for high-frequency PYTH funding strategies."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"PYTH Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PYTH funding rates on Bluefin typically range from -0.5% to +0.8% per hour, with notable negative spikes during major DeFi protocol launches or oracle integration announcements. The token shows inverse correlation with broader market funding during infrastructure-focused news cycles, creating contrarian opportunities. Historical data reveals consistent negative funding during Sui ecosystem developments and oracle partnership announcements. Monthly average funding rates tend to be slightly negative (-0.02% to -0.05% hourly) due to PYTH's utility premium in perpetual markets."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The most profitable PYTH arbitrage opportunities on Bluefin occur during oracle upgrade cycles and cross-chain expansion announcements, when funding rates can reach -1.5% hourly. Traders can exploit the premium between Bluefin's hourly funding and other exchanges' 8-hour cycles by taking opposing positions during rate divergence periods. The Sui ecosystem's lower gas costs enable profitable micro-arbitrage strategies with position sizes as small as $1,000. Cross-DEX arbitrage becomes particularly attractive when Bluefin's PYTH funding diverges from centralized exchanges by more than 0.3% on an 8-hour normalized basis."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin's relatively low PYTH volume ($50k-200k daily) can create slippage risks for positions above $5,000, particularly during funding rate spikes. The Sui ecosystem's early stage introduces smart contract and bridge risks that don't exist on established chains. Funding rate reversals can be sharp and unpredictable, with PYTH rates swinging from -1% to +0.8% within single hours during volatile oracle market conditions. Traders should maintain strict position sizing and monitor Sui network performance, as congestion can delay funding payments and create temporary arbitrage disruptions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are PYTH funding rates updated on Bluefin?","answer":"Bluefin updates PYTH funding rates every hour, with payments processed at the top of each hour. The rate calculation uses a 15-minute TWAP of the premium index to smooth short-term volatility."},{"question":"What makes PYTH funding different from other infrastructure tokens on Bluefin?","answer":"PYTH's oracle utility creates unique funding patterns with frequent negative rates during infrastructure adoption cycles. Unlike governance tokens, PYTH funding correlates with actual data usage rather than just speculation."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage PYTH funding between Bluefin and centralized exchanges?","answer":"Yes, but consider the 1-hour vs 8-hour funding frequency difference. Bluefin's hourly payments can be normalized to 8-hour equivalents for comparison, with profitable arbitrage when the normalized difference exceeds transaction costs."},{"question":"What are the main risks of holding PYTH positions on Bluefin for funding?","answer":"Key risks include Sui network congestion affecting settlements, low liquidity causing slippage on larger positions, and smart contract risks inherent to newer DeFi protocols. Always size positions according to available liquidity."}]}]
